s trace his transformations, from an immigrant newcomer to a respected townsman, a wage worker to an entrepreneur, and a bachelor to a married man.Carefully edited and fully annotated by historians Andrew C. Holman and Robert B. Kristofferson, More of a Man features an introduction providing historical context for McIlwraith's life and an epilogue detailing what happened to him after the diaries end. Historians of labour, gender, and migration in the North Atlantic world will find More of a Man a valuable primary document of considerable insight and depth. All readers will find it a lively story of life in the nineteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aBookkeeperszOntariovDiaries. 0aDrafterszOntariovDiaries. 0aPatternmakerszNew York (State)zNew YorkvDiaries. 0aPatternmakerszOntariovDiaries. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh1 aKristofferson, Robert K., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266219340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442662193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442662193.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK